@node Overview
@chapter Overview

@samp{tab-bar-extras.el} extends Emacs' built-in @code{tab-bar-mode} with a rich set of display elements and notification controls for the tab bar's global area (the right-hand side where @code{global-mode-string} is shown). Instead of relying on the mode line for status information, this package moves time, battery, notifications, and other indicators into the tab bar, freeing the mode line for buffer-specific details.

The package integrates with several external packages including @samp{doom-modeline} (for GitHub notifications and debug status), @samp{telega} (for Telegram notifications), @samp{org-pomodoro} (for timer display), @samp{display-wttr} (for weather), and @samp{calendar-extras} (for geolocation).

The main capabilities are:

@itemize
@item
@strong{Tab bar elements.} A collection of display elements for time, battery, Emacs profile, notifications, and more (@ref{Tab bar elements}).
@item
@strong{Reset and refresh.} Commands to reset the tab bar display, update geolocation and weather, and restart the clock (@ref{Resetting the tab bar}).
@item
@strong{Notification management.} Commands to toggle the visibility of GitHub and Telega notifications individually or globally (@ref{Notification management}).
@end itemize

