@node @code{tab-bar-extras-global-mode-string}
@section @code{tab-bar-extras-global-mode-string}

@vindex tab-bar-extras-global-mode-string
The user option @code{tab-bar-extras-global-mode-string} defines the list of elements displayed in the tab bar's global area. It should be set to a list containing the desired element constants and @code{:eval} forms from the tab bar elements section (@ref{Tab bar elements}). The @code{tab-bar-extras-reset} command (@ref{Resetting the tab bar}) applies this value to @code{global-mode-string}.

The default value is @code{nil}. The type is an alist.

@node @code{tab-bar-extras-reset-wttr}
@section @code{tab-bar-extras-reset-wttr}

@vindex tab-bar-extras-reset-wttr
When set to non-nil, the @code{tab-bar-extras-reset} command (@ref{Resetting the tab bar}) will refresh weather information by calling @code{display-wttr}, provided that @code{display-wttr-mode} is active. Set this to @code{nil} if you do not use the @samp{display-wttr} package or do not want weather refreshed on each reset.

The default value is @code{t}. The type is a boolean.

@node Tab bar elements
@chapter Tab bar elements

The package defines a set of constants and evaluated forms that represent individual display elements. You compose these into the @code{tab-bar-extras-global-mode-string} list to build your tab bar layout.

