@node Basic elements
@section Basic elements

@vindex tab-bar-extras-prefix-element
@vindex tab-bar-extras-separator-element
@vindex tab-bar-extras-time-element
@vindex tab-bar-extras-emacs-profile-element
The constant @code{tab-bar-extras-prefix-element} is a single space, used as the leading separator at the start of the global area.

The constant @code{tab-bar-extras-separator-element} is the string @samp{" | "}, used to separate adjacent elements. Note that conditional elements like the Telega and GitHub notifications include their own leading separator so that it disappears when the element is hidden.

The constant @code{tab-bar-extras-time-element} displays the current time from @code{display-time-string}, styled with the @code{faces-extras-display-time} face (from @samp{faces-extras.el}). To change the time format, customize @code{display-time-format}.

The constant @code{tab-bar-extras-emacs-profile-element} displays the base name of @code{user-emacs-directory}, providing a quick indicator of which Emacs profile is active.

@node System status elements
@section System status elements

@vindex tab-bar-extras-battery-element
@vindex tab-bar-extras-debug-element
The constant @code{tab-bar-extras-battery-element} displays battery status using @code{battery-status-function}. It shows a plug icon when charging and a battery icon otherwise, followed by the charge percentage.

The constant @code{tab-bar-extras-debug-element} displays active debugger states (DAP, Edebug, @code{debug-on-error}, @code{debug-on-quit}) using Doom Modeline helper functions. It only appears when at least one debug mode is active, preceded by a separator.

@node Notification elements
@section Notification elements

@vindex tab-bar-extras-telega-element
@vindex tab-bar-extras-github-element
@vindex tab-bar-extras-pomodoro-element
@vindex tab-bar-extras-notification-status-element
The constant @code{tab-bar-extras-telega-element} displays the Telega unread message count from @code{telega-mode-line-string}. It is only visible when @code{tab-bar-extras-telega-notifications-enabled} is non-nil, the Telega server is live, and there are unread messages (@ref{Notification management}).

The constant @code{tab-bar-extras-github-element} displays the GitHub notification count from @code{doom-modeline--github-notification-number}, using Doom Modeline icons and faces. It requires @code{doom-modeline-github} to be non-nil and is controlled by @code{tab-bar-extras-github-notifications-enabled} (@ref{Notification management}). Counts above 99 are displayed as ``99+''.

The constant @code{tab-bar-extras-pomodoro-element} ensures the @code{org-pomodoro-mode-line} element is present in @code{global-mode-string}, adding it if missing. This keeps the Pomodoro timer visible in the tab bar.

The constant @code{tab-bar-extras-notification-status-element} displays a muted bell icon followed by a separator when @code{tab-bar-extras-notifications-enabled} is @code{nil}, serving as a visual reminder that notifications are suppressed.

