@node Resetting the tab bar
@section Resetting the tab bar

@findex tab-bar-extras-reset
@findex tab-bar-extras-quick-reset
Over time, the tab bar display can become stale---the clock might freeze, weather data might be outdated, or the global mode string might have been modified by another package. The command @code{tab-bar-extras-reset} performs a full refresh:

@enumerate
@item
It restarts the clock with @code{display-time}.
@item
It reapplies @code{tab-bar-extras-global-mode-string} to @code{global-mode-string}.
@item
Unless the QUICK argument is non-nil, it updates geolocation via @code{calendar-extras-set-geolocation} (if @samp{calendar-extras} is loaded and @code{calendar-extras-use-geolocation} is set) and sets the weather location accordingly.
@item
If @code{tab-bar-extras-reset-wttr} is non-nil and @code{display-wttr-mode} is active, it refreshes the weather display.
@end enumerate

The command @code{tab-bar-extras-quick-reset} calls @code{tab-bar-extras-reset} with QUICK set to @code{t}, skipping the geolocation and weather steps for a faster refresh.

@findex tab-bar-extras-reset-unless-clock
The function @code{tab-bar-extras-reset-unless-clock} calls @code{tab-bar-extras-reset} only when @code{org-clock} is not currently running. This is intended for use in periodic timers: resetting the tab bar would remove the clocked task display, so this function avoids that disruption.

@node Notification management
@section Notification management

@findex tab-bar-extras-toggle-notifications
@findex tab-bar-extras-enable-all-notifications
@findex tab-bar-extras-disable-all-notifications
@findex tab-bar-extras-toggle-telega-notifications
@findex tab-bar-extras-toggle-github-notifications
The command @code{tab-bar-extras-toggle-notifications} toggles all notification elements on or off. It calls the individual toggle functions for GitHub and Telega and updates the master flag @code{tab-bar-extras-notifications-enabled}. An optional ACTION argument (@code{'enable} or @code{'disable}) forces a specific state instead of toggling.

For convenience, @code{tab-bar-extras-enable-all-notifications} and @code{tab-bar-extras-disable-all-notifications} call @code{tab-bar-extras-toggle-notifications} with the corresponding action. These are useful in focus-mode hooks or do-not-disturb workflows.

The functions @code{tab-bar-extras-toggle-telega-notifications} and @code{tab-bar-extras-toggle-github-notifications} control their respective notification elements individually. Each accepts an optional ACTION argument. They update the variables @code{tab-bar-extras-telega-notifications-enabled} and @code{tab-bar-extras-github-notifications-enabled} and display a confirmation message.

@node Functions
@chapter Functions

@menu
* Helper functions::
@end menu

@node Helper functions
@section Helper functions

@findex tab-bar-extras-set-global-mode-string
@findex tab-bar-extras-toggle-individual-notifications
@findex tab-bar-extras-get-state
The function @code{tab-bar-extras-set-global-mode-string} sets @code{global-mode-string} to the value of @code{tab-bar-extras-global-mode-string} (@ref{@code{tab-bar-extras-global-mode-string}, , User options}). Messages are suppressed during this operation.

The function @code{tab-bar-extras-toggle-individual-notifications} is the shared implementation behind @code{tab-bar-extras-toggle-telega-notifications} and @code{tab-bar-extras-toggle-github-notifications} (@ref{Notification management}). It updates the given variable and displays a status message.

The function @code{tab-bar-extras-get-state} determines the new boolean state based on an ACTION argument (@code{'enable} returns @code{t}, @code{'disable} returns @code{nil}) or the current value of VAR (toggling it). It is used internally by the notification toggle functions.

